  "Description": "COPYRIGHT 2005 BLUE CROSS/BLUE SHIELD OF KANSAS CITY \n\n\nJOB NAME:\n                               EdwSubgrpRateExtr\n\nDESCRIPTION:  \n                               Pulls data from IDS and codes hash file, combines and loads data into the EDW\n\nINPUTS:\n                               IDS:  SUBGRP_RATE\n  \nHASH FILES:\n                               hf_cdma_codes - Load the CDMA codes to get cd from cd_sk\n\n\nTRANSFORMS:  \n                               TRIM all the fields that are extracted or used in lookups\n                           \nPROCESSING:\n                               IDS - read from source, lookup all code SK values and get the natural codes\n\nOUTPUTS: \n                               SUBGRP_RATE_D sequential file\n\nMODIFICATIONS:\n                               Hugh Sisson - 12/23/2005 - Original Program\n                               Suzanne Saylor  04/12/2006 - Added RunCycle parameter, set LAST_RUN_CYC_EXCTN_SK to RunCycle\n\n\nMODIFICATIONS:\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                DATASTAGE               CODE                           DATE\nDEVELOPER             DATE                PROJECT                     DESCRIPTION                                                                                      ENVIRONMENT          REVIEWER                 REVIEW\n-----------------------------    ----------------------     ------------------------------        -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  ------------------------------    ------------------------------       --------------------\nBalkarn Gill               07/11/2013        5114                              Create Load File for EDW Table SUBGRP_RATE_D                             EnterpriseWhseDevl\n\nAnnotations:\nJob Name: IdsEdwSubgrpRateDExtr\nRead from source table P_CAE_MBR_PRMCY and PROV from IDS.  Apply Run Cycle filters when applicable to get just the needed rows forward\nWrite MBR_PRMCY_D Data into a Sequential file for Load Job IdsEdwSubgrpRateDimLoad.\nAdd Defaults and Null Handling."
